This paper deals with optimization algorithms, specifically in the context of machine learning. The use of Gaussian processes and Upper Confidence Bound (UCB) algorithms suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of comparisons and constrained optimization suggests a focus on optimization and decision making (cs.DS). The mention of information gain and theoretical guarantees suggests a focus on neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the mention of experimental results suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
